cppglob
------------------------------------------
cppglob is a C++ port of Python glob module.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libcppglob-devel-1.1.0-1bl2
  libcppglob1-1.1.0-1bl2
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Kogia-sima/cppglob

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Kogia-sima/cppglob/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cppglob-1.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cppglob-1.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cppglob-1.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cppglob-1.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcppglob1-1.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcppglob-devel-1.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cppglob)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cppglob.README
  /usr/share/doc/cppglob/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/cppglob/README.md

(libcppglob1)
  /usr/bin/cygcppglob-1.dll

(libcppglob-devel)
  /usr/include/cppglob/config.hpp
  /usr/include/cppglob/fnmatch.hpp
  /usr/include/cppglob/glob.hpp
  /usr/include/cppglob/glob_iterator.hpp
  /usr/include/cppglob/iglob.hpp
  /usr/lib/cmake/cppglob/cppglob-config-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/cppglob/cppglob-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/libcppglob.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/cppglob.pc

